   {:e #blake3 "f2c3eaf4123001d9d276da3097c0106aaa1b7ae64cf6c74af03715184b8b6958" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "RADICAL INSIGHT: The extractor concept generalizes far beyond programming languages. An extractor is any process that observes reality and produces datoms. The most powerful extractors may not be about code at all. Consider: (1) LLM-AS-EXTRACTOR: An AI agent reads a codebase and produces :component/* datoms with semantic understanding — not just syntactic module declarations but CONCEPTUAL components (this function implements auth, that module handles payment). No static analyzer can do this. The LLM IS the universal language extractor. (2) HUMAN-AS-EXTRACTOR: A developer runs braid observe and their observations become datoms. Humans are already extractors — we just need to recognize this. (3) RUNTIME-AS-EXTRACTOR: Instrument the running system, capture actual call graphs/code paths as :composition/* datoms. Production reality, not static approximation. (4) CONVERSATION-AS-EXTRACTOR: Parse conversation transcripts (design sessions, code reviews, standup notes) and extract decisions, intentions, constraints as datoms. The conversation IS data. These aren't future-state dreams — they're natural extensions of an architecture where the store is the universal bus.; THE DEEPEST INSIGHT: Every tool call the agent makes flows through the MCP server. The MCP server ALREADY sees: which files were read (interest signal), which queries were run (understanding signal), which tests were run (verification signal), which braid commands were called (methodology signal), temporal patterns (session phase). These are extraction signals that currently produce ZERO datoms. The MCP server is the universal observation point — it just needs an extraction layer. Not a separate extractor binary. Not a config system. The MCP server that's already running IS the universal extractor. It sees everything the agent does. It just needs to produce datoms from what it sees. The conversation IS the extraction session. The tool call stream IS the raw data. The store IS the persistent understanding.; MCP Server as Continuous Extractor; No False Certainty from Behavioral Extraction; Multi-Layer Evidence Composition over Single-Extractor Precision; Evidence Lattice for Extracted Datoms" :op :assert}
